<div class="container">
    <div class="column is-10 is-offset-1">
        <article class="message is-info">
            <div class="message-header jobb-header">
                <p class="title is-4 has-text-white has-text-weight-light">
                    Do you have a passion for doing business and want to know what it is like to work at H&M?
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="message-body has-text-black">
                <strong>
                    Do you have a passion for doing business and want to know what it is like to work at H&M? Do
                    you want to participate in our journey expanding into new markets, developing exciting new
                    brands and creating the best customer offer? Then you should apply for our Summer internship!
                </strong>
                <br />
                <br />
                <p class="subtitle">THE INTERNSHIP</p>
                As a Summer Intern at H&M you will get the opportunity to share your ideas and take initiatives in
                order to affect our business on a global level. You will work in diversified teams where your major task
                will be business driven analysis to maximize sales and profitability. During the summer you will work
                as Business Controller within one of our global functions; Buying Office, Sales & Operations, Online
                Sales or New Business at our Head Office in Stockholm, Sweden.
                The internship is designed to give you an understanding for our core business and to start building a
                network within our organization. You will get a mentor that will introduce you to H&M and your role as
                Business Controller, you will attend several seminars held by our leaders and work as a Sales Advisor
                in our stores. During the internship you will also work with a concrete case that will make a difference
                for your team and the business, which you will present in the end of the program.
                Throughout the internship you will get the possibility to work with your development and we see the
                internship as a mutual job interview. You will get to know H&M from the inside and we will get the
                opportunity to evaluate you for future positions as Business Controller within the function you will
                belong to. We are looking for driven talents who are eager to make a difference and want to grow with
                us, and many of our former Summer Interns are today leaders within our fast-expanding global
                organization, both in Sweden and around the world.
                <br />
                <br />
                <p class="subtitle">YOUR PROFILE</p>
                • Business or Engineering students with one year left to graduation after the internship.
                <br />
                • Strong analytical skills and the ability to turn your analysis into actions that will affect the business.
                <br />
                • Driven and result oriented, with a genuine interest in retail.
                <br />
                • An entrepreneurial mind-set, taking own initiatives, as we are a flat organization with a straight
                forward, open-minded culture and short decision paths.
                <br />
                • Team players with leadership skills wanting to grow as leaders within H&M.
                <br />
                • Experience in sales, store or e-commerce is meritorious.
                <br />
                • International experience from either work or studies. Your English is fluent and other languages are
                meritorious. Swedish is not mandatory.
                <br />
                To be eligible you need to have work permit in Sweden or EU.
                <br>
                <br>
                <p class="subtitle">APPLY</p>
                Are you up for the challenge? Apply no later than 27th of November 2017 via the link below. Please
                send your application in English including CV, cover letter, high school and university grades
                (including description of grading system).
                <br>
                <br>
                <a class="button is-link is-outlined" href="https://career.hm.com/content/hmcareer/sv_se/findjob/jobs/imported/2017/10/3/00212262.html" target="_blank">
                    <span class="icon is-small">
                        <i class="fa fa-external-link"></i>
                    </span>
                    <span>Apply here!</span>
                </a>
                <br />
                <br />
                H&M will review all complete applications and will get back to you as soon as possible in December, after
                the last application day. Selected candidates will be given analytical web-tests as a first step between 8th-
                11th of December. If we believe you have what it takes, you will be invited to assessment days at our Head
                Office in Stockholm the 17-19th of January 2018. You have to be able to participate during these dates to
                apply for the program.
                If you have any questions with regards to the application, please see our FAQ. If you can’t find your
                answer there, email us at; summerinternship@hm.com
                <br />
                <br />
                The Summer Internship will run from 7th of June until 20st of July 2018.
                We look forward to your application!
                Read more about the Summer Internship Program and meet former Summer Interns:
                <br />
                <a class="button is-link is-outlined" href="https://career.hm.com/content/hmcareer/en_se/student/education1/summer-internship.html" 
                   target="_blank">Read more</a>
                <br />
                <br />
                <p class="has-text-weight-light">H&M is a world leading fashion retailer, with more than 161.000 employees and 4400 stores, in
                    over 68 markets and 43 online markets. H&M Group also includes COS, Weekday, Monki, Cheap
                    Monday,& Other Stories, H&M Home and Arket. Our business idea is fashion and quality at the
                    best price in a sustainable way.
                </p>
                <div class="has-text-centered">
                    <img src="~/images/jobs-by-hm.gif" />
                </div> 
            </div>
        </article>
